</section><section class="exercises" data-depth="1" id="fs-idp25531728"><h3 data-type="document-title" id="[redacted for uniqueness]"><span class="os-number">21.3</span><span class="os-divider"> </span><span class="os-text">Radioactive Decay</span></h3>
<div class=" os-hasSolution " data-type="exercise" id="fs-idp13838752">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-idm89930880"><a class="os-number" href="chapter-21#fs-idp13838752-solution">19</a><span class="os-divider">. </span><div class="os-problem-container">
<p id="fs-idm10223552">What are the types of radiation emitted by the nuclei of radioactive elements?</p>
</div></div>

</div>
<div class=" " data-type="exercise" id="fs-idp81671360">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-idp17293680"><span class="os-number">20</span><span class="os-divider">. </span><div class="os-problem-container">
<p id="fs-idm2773856">What changes occur to the atomic number and mass of a nucleus during each of the following decay scenarios?</p>
<p id="fs-idp137675104">(a) an α particle is emitted</p>
<p id="fs-idp36662256">(b) a β particle is emitted</p>
<p id="fs-idp5160032">(c) γ radiation is emitted</p>
<p id="fs-idp138318864">(d) a positron is emitted</p>
<p id="fs-idp30872480">(e) an electron is captured</p>
</div></div>
</div>
<div class=" os-hasSolution " data-type="exercise" id="fs-idp50277600">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-idp176495056"><a class="os-number" href="chapter-21#fs-idp50277600-solution">21</a><span class="os-divider">. </span><div class="os-problem-container">
